'''Institute for Nuclear Research and Nuclear Energy''' (INRNE) of the '''[[Bulgarian Academy of Sciences]]''' is the leading center for research and application of the [[nuclear physics]] in [[Bulgaria]].
The research areas include: * Theory of the [[elementary particle]]s, [[string theory]], theory of [[Atomic nucleus|atomic nuclei]], [[soliton]] interactions and [[quantum]] phenomena * [[Experimental physics]] of the elementary particles * Gamma-[[astrophysics]] at very high energies * [[Nuclear reaction]]s, structure of atomic nuclei * [[Neutron]] interactions and cross sections, physics of the [[Nuclear fission|fission]] * Reactor physics, [[nuclear power|nuclear energy]] and [[nuclear safety]] and security * [[Dosimetry]] and radiation safety * Monitoring and management of the [[Natural environment|environment]], [[radioecology]] * [[Radiochemistry]], high precision analyses of substances, development and production of radioactive sources * Nuclear and neutron methods for investigations of substances * Nuclear instrument design and production
The Institute's staff of about 320 (150 of them are [[scientific research]]ers) works in 16 laboratories, 2 scientific experimental facilities and 9 departments providing general support activities.
